SUMMARY:Job Interview Essentials
DTSTAMP:20260413T004143Z
DTSTART:20260414T203000Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday\, April 14\, 2026\, 1:30 - 3pm\n\nThis interactive pres
	entation covers essential techniques to help you make a positive and lasti
	ng impression at your next job interview.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Lib
	rary\n\nRoom Location: Level 4 - Room 2\n\nRegistration Required: Registra
	tion is not required.\n\nDetailed Description: Prepare to shine in your ne
	xt job interview with Employment Specialist\n\nCorey Minatani\n\nfrom Ever
	green Goodwill's Job Training and Education Center \\(JTEC\\). Learn how t
	o answer common interview questions\, handle challenging scenarios\, and p
	resent yourself with confidence and professionalism. Corey will provide ac
	tionable tips and strategies to help you communicate your strengths and le
	ave employers eager to hire you.\, Whether you're new to the workforce or 
	looking to refine your skills\, this workshop is your key to interview suc
	cess.\, Thanks to our partner\n\nEvergreen Goodwill Job Training & Educati
	on.\n\nEvent Logistics: There will be time after the presentation to ask q
	uestions.\, Find out more about our\n\nEmployment Workshops .\n\nContact U
	s: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4
	636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people with 
	disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven da
	ys before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library programs are 
	free and open to the public.\,\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/de
	tails/job-interview-essentials/18572333/2026-04-14T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - L
	earning & Education
