BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:_bhW5iIyOr22twOs-oOE-
SUMMARY:Housing Justice: From Policy to Practice
DTSTAMP:20260413T004144Z
DTSTART:20260424T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join YWCA Seattle | King | Snohomish for Housing Justice: From 
	Policy to Practice\, a virtual panel focusing on the ways housing policies
	 show up in real life. We will explore what's working and what's not\, and
	 the changes needed to ensure safe\, stable\, and affordable housing for a
	ll people across King and Snohomish Counties.\n\nHear from a group of comm
	unity leaders\, advocates\, and service providers\, as they ground the con
	versation in local context\, share the realities of implementation\, and e
	levate solutions that center equity\, accountability\, lived experience\, 
	and community voice.\n\nFeatured speakers for this event are:\n\n- Gregory
	 Davis\, Rainier Beach Action Coalition\n\n- Colleen Echohawk\, Community 
	Roots Housing\n\n- Alison Eisinger\, Seattle/King County Coalition on Home
	lessness\n\n- Estela Ortega\, El Centro de la Raza\n\n- Mindy Woods\, Snoh
	omish County Human Services \\(facilitator\\)\n\nAbout Until Justice Just 
	Is\n\nThis year marks the 15th anniversary of this annual event\, formerly
	 known as Stand Against Racism and hosted by the People of Color Executive
	 Council of YWCA Seattle | King | Snohomish.\n\nA signature campaign of YW
	CA USA Until Justice Just Is invites communities across the country to com
	e together with YWCA to raise awareness about the impacts of racism and to
	 build community among those working for racial justice.\n\nhttps://seatod
	ay.6amcity.com/events/#/details/housing-justice-from-policy-to-practice/18
	524086/2026-04-24T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Education
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/housing-justice-from-poli
	cy-to-practice/18524086/2026-04-24T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
